- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper presents a real-time dense mapping algorithm using fisheye cameras for 3D scene perception, which is a core topic in computer vision.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper focuses on self-driving vehicles and their perception of the environment, which is a key area of research in robotics.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses the YOLOv3 object detection framework, which is a popular deep learning model for object detection.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper presents an algorithm for autonomous perception of the environment, which is a key area of research in AI.
- cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper presents a novel approach for dense mapping using fisheye cameras, which is a topic of interest in the CVPR community.
